<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 12 at 4:10AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Areas of Fog Affecting portions of Deep South Texas...
Surface observations indicate that areas of fog have developed
across portions of Brooks, Jim Hogg, and Zapata Counties early
this morning. Visibilities will generally range around 1 mile in
the fog, with some patchy dense fog reducing the visibility to 1/2
of a mile or less in some areas.
Motorists are urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and
avoid following other vehicles too closely in the areas of denser
fog through the early morning hours.</description>
